1
00:01:25,870 --> 00:01:34,990
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:37,880
[Episode 32]

3
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:40,720
Zhuang,

4
00:01:41,180 --> 00:01:41,840
the shipments are all out.

5
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,100
What are you busy with?

6
00:01:43,420 --> 00:01:44,200
Weren't we hit hard

7
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:46,000
by counterfeit goods recently?

8
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:49,890
I'm working on
a new anti-counterfeiting method.

9
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:53,590
This is a big deal.

10
00:01:53,620 --> 00:01:55,080
You have to get this right.

11
00:01:57,890 --> 00:01:58,620
By the way...

12
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:03,570
Xu mentioned yesterday

13
00:02:03,570 --> 00:02:05,300
that your grandmother is sick.

14
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:08,630
Just a small token.

15
00:02:08,690 --> 00:02:09,530
It's not much.

16
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:10,310
No, no.

17
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:10,990
No, Zhuang.

18
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,120
I can't take this money.

19
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:12,630
You and Mr. Xu

20
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:13,650
are already tight on money.

21
00:02:13,650 --> 00:02:15,510
-I really can't take it.
-Enough.

22
00:02:15,540 --> 00:02:17,070
Her treatment comes first.

23
00:02:17,090 --> 00:02:17,960
If it's not enough,

24
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:20,090
we'll figure something out together.

25
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,579
Thank you, Zhuang.

26
00:02:23,280 --> 00:02:24,020
Help me watch the shop.

27
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,350
I need to go out for a bit.

28
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,300
Mr. Xu, Zhuang.

29
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:27,180
What did Chen Guangfa promise you?

30
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,190
Did he say

31
00:03:29,270 --> 00:03:30,590
that after ruining our business,

32
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:31,590
this place

33
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:33,640
would be handed over to you?

34
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,090
Mr. Xu, what did you say?

35
00:03:39,090 --> 00:03:40,210
You've got me all wrong.

36
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:41,670
Then what are you copying?

37
00:03:42,410 --> 00:03:44,190
I...

38
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:47,280
You still don't know

39
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,700
how your store went out
of business, do you?

40
00:03:59,650 --> 00:04:00,630
[Product Return Form]

41
00:04:02,930 --> 00:04:05,550
[Order Confirmation Receipt]

42
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:08,810
Isn't this

43
00:04:08,810 --> 00:04:10,670
the batch that got canceled on me?

44
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:12,800
You already suspected back then

45
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,800
that it was malicious competition.

46
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:16,760
But you never thought through

47
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,060
why that person

48
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:18,760
could know

49
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,399
your restock timing
and pricing so precisely.

50
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:23,650
You mean

51
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:27,720
the one who ruined me

52
00:04:29,690 --> 00:04:30,850
was Chen Guangfa?

53
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:33,810
The same way he brought you down back then

54
00:04:33,810 --> 00:04:35,770
is how he plans to take us down now.

55
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,090
You're being used as a pawn.

56
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,140
Mr. Xu, Zhuang,

57
00:04:44,010 --> 00:04:45,900
since when did you know—

58
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:47,190
That's not important.

59
00:04:51,570 --> 00:04:52,920
If you knew I was trouble,

60
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,180
then why place

61
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:55,650
that 20,000-unit order?

62
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:58,530
Those 20,000 units

63
00:04:58,550 --> 00:04:59,920
were

64
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:01,200
for our Russian friends.

65
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:02,540
We knew early on

66
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,340
that Chen Guangfa set a trap.

67
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:06,800
What Chen Guangfa asked you to do

68
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:08,190
is illegal.

69
00:05:08,390 --> 00:05:09,760
He used you

70
00:05:09,780 --> 00:05:11,290
to keep his own hands clean.

71
00:05:11,290 --> 00:05:12,620
In the end,

72
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:14,630
you'd be the one taking the fall.

73
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:17,280
Mr. Xu, Zhuang.

74
00:05:18,410 --> 00:05:19,740
I was really used by him.

75
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,040
Really, believe me.

76
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,480
I was really used by him.

77
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:24,760
Please forgive me, okay?

78
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:26,280
I won't dare do it again.

79
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:34,900
Hello?

80
00:05:41,810 --> 00:05:43,190
Okay, got it.

81
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:45,640
Just as expected.

82
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,700
The shipment's been held at customs.

83
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:49,620
Mr. Xu.

84
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:51,990
Chen Guangfa did this.

85
00:05:53,310 --> 00:05:54,520
What do we do now?

86
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:56,380
That's 20,000 units.

87
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:57,980
What now?

88
00:05:59,990 --> 00:06:02,190
There is no customs declaration.

89
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:07,210
The declared category
is second-hand textiles.

90
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,880
Actually, they are all

91
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:12,980
newly produced export down jackets.

92
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,180
Xu, you are here.

93
00:06:31,630 --> 00:06:32,010
I heard

94
00:06:32,010 --> 00:06:33,740
one of your shipments got held.

95
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,420
They were about to seize it.

96
00:06:35,420 --> 00:06:36,420
I quickly asked

97
00:06:36,450 --> 00:06:37,480
Mr. Kozlov

98
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,390
to wait for you.

99
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,610
Hurry up and explain yourself.

100
00:06:39,610 --> 00:06:40,810
Is there any misunderstanding?

101
00:06:40,810 --> 00:06:42,140
Then I should thank you.

102
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,490
What a coincidence.

103
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:44,630
You're here, too.

104
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,650
I'm here to pay additional duties.

105
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,840
As business people,

106
00:06:50,070 --> 00:06:51,470
the most important thing

107
00:06:51,810 --> 00:06:53,470
is that we cannot evade taxes.

108
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:58,930
Russian Customs Notice No. 12:

109
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,340
Undeclared goods

110
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:01,910
will be confiscated.

111
00:07:02,430 --> 00:07:03,750
Wait a moment.

112
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:08,000
Hello.

113
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,200
This is our customs clearance document.

114
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,260
Please take a look.

115
00:07:12,370 --> 00:07:13,020
Okay.

116
00:07:13,810 --> 00:07:15,930
Customs clearance documents
must be checked carefully.

117
00:07:15,930 --> 00:07:17,330
There are too many fakes.

118
00:07:21,630 --> 00:07:22,630
Everything checks out.

119
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:23,840
These are your goods.

120
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:24,870
You can take them.

121
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:26,630
But we don't handle transport.

122
00:07:26,770 --> 00:07:28,750
Don't worry. I'll handle it myself.

123
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:29,380
Thank you.

124
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,390
Take them?

125
00:07:31,330 --> 00:07:32,510
These are smuggled goods.

126
00:07:32,510 --> 00:07:33,680
And you're letting him take them?

127
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,600
Who told you

128
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:37,290
my goods are smuggled?

129
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,520
I'd like to file a report.

130
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:46,150
Guangfa Commerce

131
00:07:46,570 --> 00:07:48,659
has copied MRX brand designs,

132
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:50,060
is selling counterfeit goods,

133
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:52,390
and is engaged in large-scale smuggling.

134
00:07:57,810 --> 00:07:59,820
You remind me of an ancient figure—

135
00:08:01,060 --> 00:08:01,770
Lyu Bu.

136
00:08:05,690 --> 00:08:07,020
You're very meticulous

137
00:08:07,930 --> 00:08:08,830
and smart.

138
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,530
But who can prove

139
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,610
which of the goods held at customs

140
00:08:12,770 --> 00:08:13,990
are yours

141
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,520
and which are mine?

142
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:18,230
You've been to my warehouse, right?

143
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:19,490
They're identical.

144
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:23,740
Do you really think your goods

145
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:26,130
are exactly the same as mine?

146
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:26,980
What else?

147
00:08:27,570 --> 00:08:29,310
Did you embroider flowers in the pockets?

148
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:30,020
Indeed.

149
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:31,130
I admit

150
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,580
that your goods can pass
for the real thing.

151
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:35,049
But speaking of this,

152
00:08:35,049 --> 00:08:36,120
I have to thank you.

153
00:08:39,530 --> 00:08:41,120
You were the one who said

154
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:41,870
in business,

155
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,630
you have to cut costs.

156
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,150
A successful businessman

157
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,050
must maximize profits.

158
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:48,510
And that's exactly

159
00:08:48,510 --> 00:08:49,630
what made me realize

160
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:50,910
the biggest difference

161
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:52,780
between us.

162
00:08:53,030 --> 00:08:54,350
Your goods are not bad.

163
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:55,860
They are top quality.

164
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:58,360
But the cost is too high.

165
00:08:58,490 --> 00:09:00,930
And there are taxes
and quality inspection procedures.

166
00:09:00,930 --> 00:09:01,550
To put it bluntly,

167
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:02,550
it's all for show.

168
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:05,580
Because of that,

169
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:07,650
your cost has increased by half.

170
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:09,240
Is it worth it?

171
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,030
In business,

172
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,910
you have to balance the short-term gains

173
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,570
against the long-term value.

174
00:09:15,170 --> 00:09:15,840
Mr. Chen,

175
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:20,000
why don't you also get

176
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,410
international certification?

177
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:22,790
Then all the goods outside

178
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:23,750
will be yours.

179
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:33,420
Mr. Kozlov,

180
00:09:33,590 --> 00:09:34,980
the serial numbers on this list

181
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:36,360
match the ones

182
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,160
on our labels.

183
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,290
Feel free to verify.

184
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:39,370
Indeed.

185
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:41,740
These formal quality inspections

186
00:09:41,740 --> 00:09:42,890
and customs procedures

187
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:44,400
increase costs a lot.

188
00:09:44,850 --> 00:09:46,470
But that's exactly why

189
00:09:47,530 --> 00:09:49,230
no matter how hard you scheme,

190
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:52,230
your fakes will never be real.

191
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:56,710
All right.

192
00:09:57,170 --> 00:09:58,860
I've accepted your report.

193
00:09:59,170 --> 00:09:59,970
Chen Guangfa,

194
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:02,150
you can't take your goods away for now.

195
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:04,950
You must cooperate
with our investigation first.

196
00:10:05,460 --> 00:10:06,590
China-Russia trade

197
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:08,400
still has a long way to go.

198
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:08,880
Yes.

199
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:09,620
We must

200
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:11,270
strictly inspect such matters

201
00:10:11,270 --> 00:10:12,180
in the future.

202
00:10:12,530 --> 00:10:13,870
We will absolutely not hurt

203
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:15,670
the feelings of the Chinese friends.

204
00:10:15,670 --> 00:10:16,610
Yes, yes.

205
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:17,790
Thank you.

206
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:19,210
Thank you very much.

207
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,620
So this season

208
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:36,630
comes to

209
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:37,760
a successful close.

210
00:10:38,130 --> 00:10:39,500
For the new season,

211
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:41,120
our main focus is to address

212
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:43,410
everyone's issues with down jackets...

213
00:11:05,530 --> 00:11:07,130
Alright, let's call it a day.

214
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,330
Meeting adjourned.

215
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:13,980
This house

216
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:14,840
is yours

217
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:17,910
now.

218
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:18,760
Take a look.

219
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,020
Have a seat.

220
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:25,010
When did you do the paperwork?

221
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:25,960
This morning.

222
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:28,740
Didn't you say before

223
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:31,230
[Building Ownership Certificate
of the People's Republic of China]

224
00:11:28,770 --> 00:11:29,740
you wanted to

225
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:30,950
renovate this house?

226
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:32,780
How do you want to renovate it?

227
00:11:34,940 --> 00:11:37,780
I want to divide the bedroom into two.

228
00:11:38,630 --> 00:11:39,340
Agreed.

229
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:41,510
It'll be easier

230
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:42,750
when we have a kid.

231
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:44,620
What I meant was

232
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,480
one bedroom for you and one for me.

233
00:11:46,770 --> 00:11:48,010
You snore so loudly.

234
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,620
Do you dislike me that much?

235
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:52,850
Give me the house key.

236
00:11:52,940 --> 00:11:53,510
No.

237
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:54,150
Give it back.

238
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:54,600
No.

239
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:55,320
Give me the key back.

240
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:56,190
No!

241
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:57,210
Give it back to me.

242
00:12:13,260 --> 00:12:13,820
Aren't we missing

243
00:12:13,820 --> 00:12:15,470
our certificate?

244
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:16,920
What certificate?

245
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:18,690
What certificate do you think?

246
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,340
Should we go back to Wenzhou

247
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:24,070
or Yantai for the certificate?

248
00:12:24,440 --> 00:12:25,500
I'll listen to you.

249
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,640
Okay, then we'll go back tomorrow.

250
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:31,320
I still have a meeting tomorrow.

251
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,000
A meeting?

252
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:33,840
Then,

253
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:36,580
why don't we "have a meeting" first?

254
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:46,020
[Fortune]

255
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,790
Come on, tourists,

256
00:13:54,790 --> 00:13:55,960
keep up with me.

257
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:58,840
Just a bit further ahead

258
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,640
and we'll reach the Seine River.

259
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:02,530
You can take out your cameras now

260
00:14:02,530 --> 00:14:04,390
to snap some photos for memories.

261
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,550
Stay close, don't fall behind.

262
00:14:09,170 --> 00:14:12,030
Look, those pigeons
aren't afraid of people at all.

263
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:26,710
♪ I heard you sleep alone now ♪

264
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:30,950
♪ That marriage put you through so much ♪

265
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:35,380
♪ Hearing that breaks my heart ♪

266
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:39,510
♪ Makes me want to protect you again ♪

267
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,740
♪ They say you go quiet
when I'm mentioned ♪

268
00:14:44,210 --> 00:14:47,850
♪ Always using alcohol
to sort out right and wrong ♪

269
00:14:48,330 --> 00:14:52,440
♪ I don't understand
how deep your love runs ♪

270
00:14:52,780 --> 00:14:56,620
♪ And you don't understand
how much I miss you ♪

271
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,520
[Name: Tao Liangliang]

272
00:14:58,980 --> 00:15:03,120
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

273
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:07,970
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

274
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:13,330
♪ There's too much
in this world left unresolved ♪

275
00:15:13,930 --> 00:15:17,440
♪ You're the arrow
that pierces through my longing ♪

276
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:22,050
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

277
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:26,900
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

278
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:24,020
Buddy,

279
00:15:24,460 --> 00:15:25,450
are you okay?

280
00:15:28,590 --> 00:15:32,550
♪ Looking back on those years
we held each other up ♪

281
00:15:30,370 --> 00:15:32,290
Hello.

282
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:37,520
♪ When we loved recklessly,
no matter the cost ♪

283
00:15:38,770 --> 00:15:42,850
♪ Sometimes I wonder, in this world ♪

284
00:15:38,930 --> 00:15:42,290
[Ambulance]

285
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:46,730
♪ Are there other versions of me ♪

286
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:51,300
♪ Still foolishly clinging to love ♪

287
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:52,230
Excuse me.

288
00:15:51,820 --> 00:15:55,370
♪ Clinging to other versions of you ♪

289
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:54,290
Have you seen this person?

290
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:59,540
♪ If somewhere out there ♪

291
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,310
Hurry up.

292
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,670
♪ Other versions of us exist ♪

293
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:08,350
♪ I truly hope their story ♪

294
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:13,470
♪ Gets a happy ending ♪

295
00:16:14,950 --> 00:16:18,970
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

296
00:16:20,130 --> 00:16:23,710
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

297
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,100
You can check it out over there.

298
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:25,970
Thank you.

299
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:29,320
♪ There's too much
in this world left unresolved ♪

300
00:16:30,110 --> 00:16:33,590
♪ You're the arrow
that pierces through my longing ♪

301
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:37,970
♪ Maybe we should meet again ♪

302
00:16:39,290 --> 00:16:42,860
♪ Even just for a glance ♪

303
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:47,970
♪ Looking back on those years
we held each other up ♪

304
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:53,330
♪ When we loved recklessly,
no matter the cost ♪

305
00:17:19,849 --> 00:17:20,380
Hello?

306
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:22,980
Hello, Ma'am.

307
00:17:23,530 --> 00:17:26,440
This is
the Paris 7th District Police Station.

308
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:28,800
Are you Shen Ranran?

309
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:32,850
We found a deceased Asian male,

310
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:37,140
Mr. Tao Liangliang,

311
00:17:37,310 --> 00:17:40,160
at Les Invalides Square.

312
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:42,160
When he was found,

313
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,330
he had already stopped breathing.

314
00:17:44,810 --> 00:17:46,030
We found your contact information

315
00:17:46,030 --> 00:17:47,380
in his pocket.

316
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,650
If you are a relative,

317
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:51,530
please come to assist
with the investigation

318
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:55,460
and handle his affairs within 48 hours.

319
00:19:39,750 --> 00:19:42,420
How did you end up getting this disease?

320
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:54,160
Wishing Liangliang and Ranran

321
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:56,920
a happy marriage!

322
00:20:05,940 --> 00:20:06,420
Ranran.

323
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,030
In any place

324
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,330
and in every way,

325
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:12,800
I will love you forever.

326
00:20:16,940 --> 00:20:17,800
In the future,

327
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:19,780
if anything goes down in Sijiu City

328
00:20:19,790 --> 00:20:21,710
within my power,

329
00:20:21,810 --> 00:20:23,100
just let me know.

330
00:20:31,550 --> 00:20:33,480
No one stands forever in this world.

331
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:34,750
My name is Liangliang—

332
00:20:34,980 --> 00:20:36,110
don't you forget it.

333
00:21:40,550 --> 00:21:41,810
Hello, Director Weng.

334
00:21:41,810 --> 00:21:43,210
How have you been lately?

335
00:21:43,550 --> 00:21:44,380
Xu.

336
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:46,610
I'm doing very well.

337
00:21:47,050 --> 00:21:48,560
I'm in Chengdu now.

338
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,220
The filming is about to start.

339
00:21:50,220 --> 00:21:51,950
What are you filming this time?

340
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:56,240
"The Late Love"
has finally started filming.

341
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,920
"The Late Love?"

342
00:21:58,940 --> 00:21:59,500
Yes.

343
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:00,640
You're going to shoot it?

344
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:01,140
That's right.

345
00:22:01,140 --> 00:22:02,240
Well, this is real?

346
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:03,550
Hey, Director Weng,

347
00:22:03,550 --> 00:22:04,780
what's going on?

348
00:22:04,850 --> 00:22:05,460
It's so sudden.

349
00:22:05,460 --> 00:22:06,720
I'm totally confused.

350
00:22:07,090 --> 00:22:08,290
Hey, didn't the studio

351
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:10,290
have a lot of issues with the script?

352
00:22:11,220 --> 00:22:11,960
Yes,

353
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:14,730
so I have to mention

354
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,880
your master, Mr. He.

355
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:20,290
He did a lot of work

356
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:22,870
for this film.

357
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:28,510
Hello.

358
00:22:29,380 --> 00:22:30,180
Director Gao.

359
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,190
I am He Sheng.

360
00:22:33,510 --> 00:22:34,480
I heard

361
00:22:34,940 --> 00:22:36,420
the studio is collecting

362
00:22:36,510 --> 00:22:37,980
good original scripts.

363
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:41,000
I would like to recommend

364
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,020
the one

365
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:46,110
my apprentice and I wrote five years ago—

366
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:47,770
"The Late Love."

367
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:51,570
This is

368
00:22:51,710 --> 00:22:53,300
my last script.

369
00:22:55,090 --> 00:22:58,910
I won't be writing
any more scripts from here on out.

370
00:23:02,750 --> 00:23:04,870
If you have any suggestions,

371
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:08,400
I'll revise accordingly.

372
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:11,410
I'll go through it word by word,

373
00:23:11,410 --> 00:23:13,470
even down to every punctuation mark.

374
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,370
I really want

375
00:23:17,090 --> 00:23:18,360
it to be filmed.

376
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:33,840
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

377
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:33,550
Xu Shengli.

378
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:35,050
I've seen it.

379
00:23:35,850 --> 00:23:39,600
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

380
00:23:37,090 --> 00:23:37,690
Come here.

381
00:23:37,740 --> 00:23:38,800
Let's take a photo.

382
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,040
Go over there.

383
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,470
Ready. 1, 2, 3.

384
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:49,870
Done.

385
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:51,160
Let's take one together.

386
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:51,690
Okay.

387
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:53,120
Let me find someone to help us.

388
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:53,850
Hello.

389
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,580
Could you help us take a photo?

390
00:23:55,580 --> 00:23:57,120
-Okay.
-Thank you.

391
00:24:00,770 --> 00:24:02,290
Hey, look at the camera.

392
00:24:02,590 --> 00:24:04,420
1, 2, 3.

393
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:06,230
["The Late Love"—Now Showing
in Theaters Nationwide]

394
00:24:13,330 --> 00:24:14,180
This group of characters

395
00:24:14,180 --> 00:24:15,440
has been through so much.

396
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:16,980
Shouldn't this farewell

397
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:19,030
feel a bit more meaningful?

398
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,030
That's not refined enough.

399
00:24:21,090 --> 00:24:22,290
Think about it again.

400
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,710
God

401
00:24:25,090 --> 00:24:27,260
is the cruelest screenwriter of all.

402
00:24:29,310 --> 00:24:33,110
This is a script written

403
00:24:33,330 --> 00:24:35,720
by Xu Shengli and me together.

404
00:24:36,510 --> 00:24:37,840
It's as good as it gets.

405
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,280
Slow down. Slow down.

406
00:24:42,530 --> 00:24:44,420
Slow down.

407
00:24:53,770 --> 00:24:56,680
From now on, we will

408
00:24:56,960 --> 00:24:58,590
go our separate ways.

409
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:00,830
In this world,

410
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:06,090
a lot of things just can't be avoided.

411
00:25:08,570 --> 00:25:10,320
What we can do

412
00:25:11,310 --> 00:25:12,110
is

413
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:16,090
protect what we want,

414
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:20,570
carry what we're meant to carry,

415
00:25:22,460 --> 00:25:26,190
and keep moving forward.

416
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:35,050
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]
[Director: Weng Xingguo]

417
00:25:36,190 --> 00:25:40,920
[This film is dedicated to the memory
of Mr. He Sheng]

418
00:26:16,790 --> 00:26:23,080
[The Late Love]
[Screenwriter: He Sheng, Xu Shengli]

419
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:26,010
Cut.

420
00:26:28,700 --> 00:26:29,830
Good job, everyone.

421
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:30,510
That's a wrap.

422
00:26:30,510 --> 00:26:31,570
Thanks, Director Cui.

423
00:26:31,570 --> 00:26:32,610
Come, let's take a group photo.

424
00:26:32,610 --> 00:26:33,990
Come, everyone, come.

425
00:26:34,330 --> 00:26:36,970
Happy wrap!

426
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:09,610
[Hostel]

427
00:27:08,790 --> 00:27:09,730
Northeasterner. Happy New Year.

428
00:27:09,730 --> 00:27:10,380
Happy New Year.

429
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:11,710
You're so hardworking.

430
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:15,150
Let me plug it in and see.

431
00:27:15,150 --> 00:27:17,030
[Hostel]

432
00:27:15,450 --> 00:27:16,710
Let me check on my girl.

433
00:27:17,170 --> 00:27:18,430
She sleeps so soundly.

434
00:27:18,790 --> 00:27:20,010
Let's go back to the room. Hurry.

435
00:27:20,010 --> 00:27:23,120
[Hostel]

436
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,370
Let's go.

437
00:27:23,620 --> 00:27:28,210
[Hostel]

438
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:41,990
[2018]

439
00:27:43,250 --> 00:27:44,110
In the end,

440
00:27:44,110 --> 00:27:45,070
it's all the same no matter
who you're with.

441
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:46,740
There you go again,
making a big deal out of everything.

442
00:27:46,740 --> 00:27:47,850
Hey, have you ever stepped in

443
00:27:47,850 --> 00:27:50,140
when your son got into conflicts
with others?

444
00:27:50,140 --> 00:27:51,310
I'm the one handling everything.

445
00:27:51,310 --> 00:27:52,400
while you're the one playing the good guy.

446
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:54,060
Did I say I wouldn't handle it?

447
00:27:54,530 --> 00:27:55,990
Don't I need to make money?

448
00:27:57,550 --> 00:27:58,480
You sit here every day,

449
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:00,200
pretending you're working.

450
00:28:00,430 --> 00:28:02,360
How many times
have you been to our kids' school?

451
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:04,740
How many parent-teacher conferences
have you attended?

452
00:28:04,740 --> 00:28:05,660
Big things, small things—

453
00:28:05,660 --> 00:28:06,660
I manage them all.

454
00:28:07,980 --> 00:28:08,810
If it works, we stay.

455
00:28:08,810 --> 00:28:09,740
If not, we split.

456
00:28:13,810 --> 00:28:15,300
Honey, don't be angry.

457
00:28:15,330 --> 00:28:16,590
Don't be angry.

458
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:17,840
You just

459
00:28:18,050 --> 00:28:19,580
said what you really think.

460
00:28:21,460 --> 00:28:22,010
Look,

461
00:28:22,140 --> 00:28:23,820
are those lines even in the script?

462
00:28:23,820 --> 00:28:25,350
Isn't it written like that?

463
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:28,800
Alright.

464
00:28:29,270 --> 00:28:31,200
You don't need to run lines with me.

465
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,930
You're too into character.

466
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:37,070
I was kind enough to help you run lines.

467
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,270
You've got no conscience.

468
00:28:38,270 --> 00:28:39,280
I will keep

469
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:41,380
your great kindness in mind.

470
00:28:48,250 --> 00:28:49,580
But then again,

471
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:50,980
you're actually quite suited

472
00:28:50,980 --> 00:28:52,310
to write family dramas.

473
00:28:53,090 --> 00:28:56,090
Just listening to couples talk
like this is annoying.

474
00:28:56,110 --> 00:28:57,730
Art comes from life.

475
00:28:57,940 --> 00:28:59,270
Mr. He said

476
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:01,170
-Comes from what?
-if you want—

477
00:29:02,180 --> 00:29:03,240
It comes from life,

478
00:29:04,070 --> 00:29:05,800
but it must be higher than life.

479
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:08,570
You must fully use your imagination

480
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,470
to shape it into art.

481
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:12,240
Which parts are crafted,

482
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:13,900
and which come from real life?

483
00:29:14,270 --> 00:29:14,900
This...

484
00:29:15,500 --> 00:29:16,560
this script of mine

485
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:18,330
d-doesn't come from real life.

486
00:29:18,570 --> 00:29:19,900
It's all fictionalized.

487
00:29:19,900 --> 00:29:21,630
It... It's all fictionalized.

488
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:28,920
Your pen is so old.

489
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,480
I'll get you a new one later.

490
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:31,810
No need, I like this one.

491
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,240
But isn't  your script

492
00:29:46,510 --> 00:29:47,720
too pessimistic?

493
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:49,190
Isn't it good

494
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,050
living an ordinary life

495
00:29:50,050 --> 00:29:51,110
like the two of us?

496
00:29:55,770 --> 00:29:57,760
Being able to live an ordinary life

497
00:29:58,850 --> 00:30:00,160
is already very lucky.

498
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,220
Life is full of trivial,

499
00:30:03,250 --> 00:30:04,400
messy details,

500
00:30:05,250 --> 00:30:07,910
but that doesn't mean
there's no real love in it.

501
00:30:08,660 --> 00:30:11,670
People make different choices,

502
00:30:12,070 --> 00:30:13,730
so their fates are different.

503
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:15,910
To be honest,

504
00:30:17,110 --> 00:30:18,910
having lived for most of my life,

505
00:30:21,200 --> 00:30:22,200
I'm very content.

506
00:30:25,250 --> 00:30:26,140
You're right.

507
00:30:28,980 --> 00:30:32,650
There's more than one standard answer
to happiness.

508
00:30:37,350 --> 00:30:38,440
Right now,

509
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:40,810
I just hope our parents

510
00:30:40,810 --> 00:30:41,750
stay healthy,

511
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:44,440
and Dongdong and Chunchun

512
00:30:44,790 --> 00:30:45,810
grow up well.

513
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:48,580
That's all that matters.

514
00:30:50,270 --> 00:30:50,750
Right.

515
00:30:53,570 --> 00:30:54,870
The most important thing is that you

516
00:30:54,870 --> 00:30:55,970
don't make me mad.

517
00:30:58,350 --> 00:31:00,660
When it comes to me,
I'm the one making you mad.

518
00:31:00,660 --> 00:31:01,740
I make you mad.

519
00:31:03,140 --> 00:31:03,810
Okay.

520
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:08,290
Chunchun, give me back
my roasted fish fillets!

521
00:31:08,290 --> 00:31:09,640
Give them back!

522
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:11,850
Chunchun, give them back to me.

523
00:31:11,920 --> 00:31:12,540
Listen.

524
00:31:12,570 --> 00:31:13,510
They're fighting again.

525
00:31:13,510 --> 00:31:14,430
Don't fight!

526
00:31:14,610 --> 00:31:16,540
Grandpa, look at him.

527
00:31:17,030 --> 00:31:18,300
What's going on?

528
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,700
Chunchun took my roasted fish fillets.

529
00:31:20,830 --> 00:31:21,430
Is that so?

530
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:23,720
As an older brother,

531
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:25,740
you should give in to your little sister.

532
00:31:25,740 --> 00:31:27,230
She's already eaten a lot.

533
00:31:27,310 --> 00:31:28,740
There's only one bag left.

534
00:31:28,740 --> 00:31:29,600
Only one bag?

535
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:30,760
That's impossible.

536
00:31:30,760 --> 00:31:31,400
Go.

537
00:31:31,530 --> 00:31:33,330
-Go ask your dad for them.
-It's not like we don't have more at home.

538
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:34,270
Go ask your dad for them.

539
00:31:34,270 --> 00:31:35,180
Go. Go.

540
00:31:35,270 --> 00:31:36,270
No more fighting.

541
00:31:37,810 --> 00:31:38,530
These kids

542
00:31:38,590 --> 00:31:39,400
are exactly like Shengli

543
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:40,460
when he was little.

544
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:43,860
Dad,

545
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:45,900
are there any roasted fish fillets left?

546
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:46,410
Yes,

547
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:47,400
they're in the drawer under

548
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,860
the TV cabinet.

549
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:50,700
Dad, give them to me first.

550
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:52,330
Grandpa sent me.

551
00:31:52,610 --> 00:31:54,400
You're not a little kid anymore.

552
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:55,460
Get them yourself.

553
00:31:59,690 --> 00:32:00,320
Look,

554
00:32:01,500 --> 00:32:03,550
every time they come,
the first thing they do is call for Dad.

555
00:32:03,550 --> 00:32:04,720
And you still said
I don't care about them.

556
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:05,980
How else should I care?

557
00:32:10,680 --> 00:32:11,240
[Shichahai]

558
00:32:19,590 --> 00:32:20,780
Is this still the old

559
00:32:20,810 --> 00:32:22,210
Shichahai private room?

560
00:32:22,220 --> 00:32:22,940
It's still the original

561
00:32:22,940 --> 00:32:24,180
Shichahai private room.

562
00:32:24,180 --> 00:32:24,790
It's just that

563
00:32:24,790 --> 00:32:25,960
we knocked through

564
00:32:26,010 --> 00:32:26,600
the adjacent rooms.

565
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:27,550
This way, your dining experience

566
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:28,750
will feel more spacious and comfortable,

567
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:29,280
won't it?

568
00:32:32,380 --> 00:32:33,110
Pretty good.

569
00:32:33,790 --> 00:32:34,410
Mr. Xu,

570
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:36,290
not only has our hotel
been recently renovated,

571
00:32:36,290 --> 00:32:36,980
but we have also

572
00:32:36,980 --> 00:32:38,580
introduced many new dishes.

573
00:32:38,590 --> 00:32:41,110
We have "Abundant Wealth",
"Rolling in Money",

574
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:42,700
"Happy Marriage", "Pure and Clear",

575
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:44,900
"Rising High," and "Flying Together."

576
00:32:45,610 --> 00:32:47,410
I want to eat Beijing roast duck,

577
00:32:47,900 --> 00:32:49,500
braised pork balls in gravy,

578
00:32:49,810 --> 00:32:52,510
shredded pork with sweet bean sauce,
braised pork joint,

579
00:32:52,510 --> 00:32:54,900
braised mutton strips, quick-boiled tripe,

580
00:32:54,900 --> 00:32:57,450
and old Beijing noodles
with soybean paste.

581
00:32:57,830 --> 00:32:58,410
Sir,

582
00:32:58,440 --> 00:32:59,940
the dishes I just mentioned

583
00:32:59,940 --> 00:33:00,790
are exactly

584
00:33:00,830 --> 00:33:02,110
the classic Beijing dishes you asked for.

585
00:33:02,110 --> 00:33:03,350
We just changed the names.

586
00:33:03,350 --> 00:33:04,460
Just keeping up with the times.

587
00:33:04,460 --> 00:33:05,920
We just changed the names.

588
00:33:06,090 --> 00:33:08,110
Okay, as long as you have them.

589
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:10,610
So we're still booking lunch

590
00:33:10,610 --> 00:33:11,940
for tomorrow, right?

591
00:33:13,640 --> 00:33:14,200
Right.

592
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:17,770
Our people will all be here tomorrow.

593
00:33:22,050 --> 00:33:24,110
Mr. Guo, have something to eat first.

594
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:29,290
Is this your first day at work?

595
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:32,270
When have I ever eaten stuff like this?

596
00:33:32,270 --> 00:33:33,460
Isn't it a waste?

597
00:33:35,830 --> 00:33:36,610
I'll eat it.

598
00:33:38,700 --> 00:33:40,360
Xiaobao is really something.

599
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:42,520
He even got himself a secretary.

600
00:33:44,070 --> 00:33:44,730
Drink this.

601
00:33:46,740 --> 00:33:47,800
Thank you, Mr. Guo.

602
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:56,500
Have some of this.

603
00:34:01,660 --> 00:34:02,690
Hello.

604
00:34:02,790 --> 00:34:05,610
Pizza, rice, or a hamburger?

605
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:06,740
Rice.

606
00:34:06,810 --> 00:34:07,680
Rice.

607
00:34:07,850 --> 00:34:08,420
Okay.

608
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:13,719
Hello, ma'am.

609
00:34:14,110 --> 00:34:15,710
What would you like to order?

610
00:34:18,940 --> 00:34:20,230
[Steak]

611
00:34:18,980 --> 00:34:19,510
This one.

612
00:34:20,050 --> 00:34:20,500
Then, how would you like

613
00:34:20,500 --> 00:34:22,040
your steak cooked?

614
00:34:23,170 --> 00:34:23,830
Well done.

615
00:34:25,260 --> 00:34:26,000
Are you sure?

616
00:34:29,980 --> 00:34:30,780
Are you trying to be difficult?

617
00:34:30,780 --> 00:34:32,179
I want it well-done.

618
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:33,650
Give me a well-done one.

619
00:34:33,650 --> 00:34:34,530
Heat it up right now.

620
00:34:34,530 --> 00:34:35,130
Remake it.

621
00:34:36,710 --> 00:34:37,150
Yes.

622
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:38,460
Okay.

623
00:35:01,090 --> 00:35:01,970
Honey.

624
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:03,920
Did I scare you?

625
00:35:04,170 --> 00:35:05,330
Wait inside.

626
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:06,020
It's fine.

627
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:06,920
Hey, it's not fine.

628
00:35:06,920 --> 00:35:08,260
You've been waiting forever.

629
00:35:08,260 --> 00:35:09,340
And you're wearing high heels.

630
00:35:09,340 --> 00:35:10,800
You'll be exhausted soon.

631
00:35:10,940 --> 00:35:12,340
I want to wait right here.

632
00:35:15,010 --> 00:35:17,380
Alright, then I'll wait with you.

633
00:35:18,690 --> 00:35:19,260
Okay.

634
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:31,510
Zhuang, Mr. Xu.

635
00:35:37,850 --> 00:35:38,460
In the blink of an eye,

636
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:39,890
over a decade has passed.

637
00:35:42,670 --> 00:35:44,240
You haven't changed a bit.

638
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:46,540
You've gotten so thin.

639
00:35:46,870 --> 00:35:49,330
He hasn't been giving you
a hard time, has he?

640
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:50,550
Come on, after all these years,

641
00:35:50,550 --> 00:35:52,050
neither of you has changed.

642
00:35:52,050 --> 00:35:54,050
You both are still pretty and young.

643
00:35:55,250 --> 00:35:55,800
Ranran.

644
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:57,110
Are you leaving again this time?

645
00:35:57,110 --> 00:35:57,900
Now that I'm back,

646
00:35:57,900 --> 00:35:59,360
I'll stay and work in Beijing,

647
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,610
so I can take care of the elders.

648
00:36:00,610 --> 00:36:01,850
That's wonderful.

649
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:02,940
Then...

650
00:36:03,300 --> 00:36:05,030
Then, we can see each other often.

651
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:05,990
Of course.

652
00:36:06,190 --> 00:36:06,820
In that case,

653
00:36:06,820 --> 00:36:08,460
you two can see each other every day.

654
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:09,860
You two can even live together.

655
00:36:09,860 --> 00:36:11,080
Don't be jealous.

656
00:36:11,110 --> 00:36:13,030
I won't be jealous. Me, jealous?

657
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:15,410
The great screenwriter and big star—

658
00:36:15,410 --> 00:36:16,340
You're all here?

659
00:36:16,710 --> 00:36:18,230
Little Northeasterner, the big boss.

660
00:36:18,230 --> 00:36:19,550
A small boss. A small boss.

661
00:36:19,550 --> 00:36:20,480
Long time no see.

662
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:21,340
Long time no see.

663
00:36:21,340 --> 00:36:22,500
Big star?

664
00:36:22,610 --> 00:36:24,050
I changed careers a long time ago.

665
00:36:24,050 --> 00:36:24,840
You will always be

666
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:26,440
the big star of Seasons Change Hostel.

667
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,200
In my heart,

668
00:36:27,230 --> 00:36:28,340
none of the current stars

669
00:36:28,340 --> 00:36:29,500
can compare to you.

670
00:36:29,880 --> 00:36:30,660
I heard

671
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:31,840
you've turned Seasons Change Hostel

672
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:32,980
into a big hotel.

673
00:36:33,730 --> 00:36:34,670
I opened a new place.

674
00:36:34,670 --> 00:36:35,960
It's just a small hotel.

675
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,670
What about
the original Seasons Change Hostel?

676
00:36:37,670 --> 00:36:38,410
The new place

677
00:36:38,440 --> 00:36:40,120
is managed by our chairman.

678
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:40,830
As for me,

679
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:41,950
if I have time,

680
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:43,070
I still like staying

681
00:36:43,070 --> 00:36:44,930
at our old Seasons Change Hostel.

682
00:36:45,130 --> 00:36:45,690
Yeah.

683
00:36:46,510 --> 00:36:47,600
That's our roots.

684
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,340
Without Seasons Change Hostel,

685
00:36:49,340 --> 00:36:50,820
we wouldn't be who we are today.

686
00:36:50,820 --> 00:36:51,280
Yes.

687
00:36:52,670 --> 00:36:53,870
For the meal today,

688
00:36:53,960 --> 00:36:55,380
Little Northeasterner
should take the seat of honor.

689
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:56,500
How can I take the seat of honor?

690
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:57,320
I'm so young.

691
00:36:57,530 --> 00:36:58,690
What do you mean, young?

692
00:36:58,690 --> 00:37:00,380
You must take the seat of honor.
You're paying.

693
00:37:00,380 --> 00:37:02,460
Sure, I can pay.

694
00:37:02,530 --> 00:37:03,280
But let me tell you,

695
00:37:03,280 --> 00:37:04,320
you're always welcome

696
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:05,820
to stay at our hotel anytime.

697
00:37:05,820 --> 00:37:06,380
Okay then.

698
00:37:06,380 --> 00:37:07,230
When we go,

699
00:37:07,260 --> 00:37:08,960
we'll still just give him six yuan.

700
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,250
I'm fine with that.

701
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:10,720
Chairman.

702
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:12,030
-Is that Okay?
-Is that Okay? 6 yuan.

703
00:37:12,030 --> 00:37:13,030
I'll listen to you.

704
00:37:13,030 --> 00:37:14,160
Thanks for the face.

705
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,100
It's a deal then.

706
00:37:16,210 --> 00:37:17,790
6 yuan per bed.

707
00:37:17,940 --> 00:37:19,010
I'll sell

708
00:37:19,050 --> 00:37:19,690
my house

709
00:37:19,690 --> 00:37:21,750
and move into Seasons Change Hostel.

710
00:37:23,130 --> 00:37:25,090
Shengli.

711
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:25,890
Zongbao.

712
00:37:25,990 --> 00:37:26,840
Zhuang Zhuang.

713
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:28,300
You haven't changed a bit.

714
00:37:28,300 --> 00:37:29,300
And I'm here, too.

715
00:37:29,300 --> 00:37:30,000
Ranran.

716
00:37:30,130 --> 00:37:31,230
How are you? Good?

717
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:31,940
Good, good.

718
00:37:33,690 --> 00:37:34,630
Zongbao.

719
00:37:34,650 --> 00:37:36,090
You've moved to Beijing.

720
00:37:36,130 --> 00:37:37,750
Why are you so late?

721
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:39,970
I was halfway here

722
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,860
when I realized I forgot this corn juice.

723
00:37:41,860 --> 00:37:43,150
So I went back to get it.

724
00:37:43,650 --> 00:37:45,310
It's this year's new product.

725
00:37:45,940 --> 00:37:46,800
Have a taste.

726
00:37:47,030 --> 00:37:48,160
See if it's any good.

727
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:50,440
You changed the packaging.

728
00:37:50,440 --> 00:37:52,170
I have to keep up with the times.

729
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:54,670
Everyone is here.

730
00:37:54,670 --> 00:37:56,140
Which room are we in?

731
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,160
Still Shichahai.

732
00:38:01,090 --> 00:38:02,410
[Shichahai]

733
00:38:05,820 --> 00:38:09,030
Let's not fight today.

734
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:12,500
We are too old to fight.

735
00:38:12,760 --> 00:38:14,170
Alright, everyone's hungry.

736
00:38:14,170 --> 00:38:15,170
Let's go in.

737
00:38:15,460 --> 00:38:16,500
Let's go.

738
00:38:16,590 --> 00:38:17,140
Go inside

739
00:38:17,610 --> 00:38:18,610
and eat together.

740
00:38:19,110 --> 00:38:23,150
[Shichahai]

741
00:38:19,730 --> 00:38:20,500
After lunch,

742
00:38:20,520 --> 00:38:23,050
let's go check out
the Seasons Change Hostel.

743
00:38:29,850 --> 00:38:32,310
Luogu Hutong has really changed,
hasn't it?

744
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:34,200
Lin's bun shop

745
00:38:34,300 --> 00:38:35,110
Bun Shop.

746
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,740
is now run by his daughter.

747
00:38:37,770 --> 00:38:38,880
They have several locations now.

748
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:39,480
They even opened a branch over there.

749
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:39,960
We used to

750
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:41,160
always eat buns here.

751
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:43,630
How about

752
00:38:43,650 --> 00:38:45,360
going check out the new hotel?

753
00:38:45,530 --> 00:38:46,890
Let's go and take a look.

754
00:38:47,020 --> 00:38:48,820
Let's head back to the hostel first.

755
00:38:48,820 --> 00:38:49,750
-I agree.
-Okay.

756
00:38:50,090 --> 00:38:50,800
I also want to see

757
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:51,860
what Seasons Change Hostel

758
00:38:51,860 --> 00:38:53,090
looks like now.

759
00:38:53,580 --> 00:38:54,700
I have to say.

760
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:55,680
This whole vibe

761
00:38:55,710 --> 00:38:57,190
really takes me back

762
00:38:57,780 --> 00:39:00,050
to those days when we were all wasted,

763
00:39:00,300 --> 00:39:01,630
stumbling our way

764
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:03,610
toward Seasons Change Hostel together.

765
00:39:03,610 --> 00:39:04,730
Right now,

766
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:06,670
we are like a senior tour group

767
00:39:06,780 --> 00:39:07,980
visiting the hutong.

768
00:39:08,050 --> 00:39:09,400
What do you mean, senior?

769
00:39:09,400 --> 00:39:10,420
You are the senior here.

770
00:39:10,420 --> 00:39:11,280
I'll take a picture of

771
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:12,070
that white hair of yours.

772
00:39:12,070 --> 00:39:14,590
-The tour group is missing something.
-Let me take a photo.

773
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:15,380
A tour guide.

774
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:17,390
Are you hinting at me?

775
00:39:17,530 --> 00:39:19,370
Yes, let's see what you can do.

776
00:39:19,670 --> 00:39:22,330
Do you still remember your lines
from back then?

777
00:39:22,380 --> 00:39:24,050
I can remember them even in my sleep.

778
00:39:24,050 --> 00:39:24,670
Alright, alright.

779
00:39:24,670 --> 00:39:25,930
I-I'm recording this.

780
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:27,470
Come on, you say it.

781
00:39:28,360 --> 00:39:30,490
Come on, senior tour group, follow me.

782
00:39:30,610 --> 00:39:31,630
What senior tour group?

783
00:39:31,630 --> 00:39:33,210
North, south, all around.

784
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:35,340
Visiting kin, visiting friends.

785
00:39:35,340 --> 00:39:36,550
On business, on vacation.

786
00:39:36,550 --> 00:39:37,980
-Chasing fortune or chasing dreams—
-It's the same line.

787
00:39:37,980 --> 00:39:38,840
-It's exactly the same.
-We

788
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:39,260
Right.

789
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:41,110
come from all corners of the country.

790
00:39:41,110 --> 00:39:42,360
At Seasons Change Hostel,

791
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:43,440
we are one family.

792
00:39:43,730 --> 00:39:46,380
Seasons Change Hostel
helps your dreams come true.

793
00:39:46,380 --> 00:39:47,340
Are those the words?

794
00:39:47,340 --> 00:39:48,440
Yes.

795
00:39:51,030 --> 00:39:52,760
Come on, stay close, everyone.

796
00:39:53,900 --> 00:39:55,500
It hasn't changed much here.

797
00:39:56,670 --> 00:39:57,930
Come on, let's go home.

798
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:58,860
We're home!

799
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:10,640
[Seasons Change Hostel]

800
00:40:11,880 --> 00:40:13,090
Hurry up, come on.

801
00:40:21,630 --> 00:40:22,630
Northeasterner.

802
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:24,460
W-What are you doing?

803
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:31,590
I hurried here. I'm not late, am I?

804
00:40:39,890 --> 00:40:40,990
I'm back.

805
00:40:43,170 --> 00:40:44,350
Is everyone here?

806
00:40:44,420 --> 00:40:44,950
Hurry up.

807
00:40:52,500 --> 00:40:53,380
I'm coming.

808
00:40:55,670 --> 00:40:57,270
You're taking a group photo?

809
00:40:57,490 --> 00:40:59,020
[Seasons Change Hostel]

810
00:40:57,710 --> 00:40:58,280
Come on.

811
00:41:04,550 --> 00:41:05,570
The camera is really expensive.

812
00:41:05,570 --> 00:41:06,320
Cao?

813
00:41:06,710 --> 00:41:08,060
I'm late. I'm late.

814
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:09,680
[Seasons Change Hostel]

815
00:41:09,650 --> 00:41:10,550
I took a detour.

816
00:41:12,530 --> 00:41:13,340
Should I

817
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:16,570
[Seasons Change Hostel]

818
00:41:13,340 --> 00:41:14,890
change clothes today?

819
00:41:15,010 --> 00:41:16,390
You look very sharp.

820
00:41:17,070 --> 00:41:17,500
Isn't this your

821
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:18,210
best-looking outfit?

822
00:41:18,210 --> 00:41:19,260
Uncle Guo looks the best.

823
00:41:19,260 --> 00:41:19,860
Nonsense.

824
00:41:19,960 --> 00:41:20,960
Is everything ready?

825
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:21,980
-Come on.
-We're ready.

826
00:41:21,980 --> 00:41:22,440
Come on.

827
00:41:22,510 --> 00:41:23,510
Let's begin then.

828
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:26,570
You took a photo without me?

829
00:41:32,550 --> 00:41:38,230
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

830
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:44,550
♪ And never brought to mind? ♪

831
00:41:45,090 --> 00:41:50,770
♪ Should auld acquaintance be forgot ♪

832
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:56,800
♪ And auld lang syne? ♪

833
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:52,880
-Liangliang?
-Liangliang.

834
00:41:55,070 --> 00:41:55,960
Come here.

835
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:59,070
Liangliang.

836
00:41:57,730 --> 00:42:03,490
♪ We twa hae run about the braes ♪

837
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:01,150
You are here?

838
00:42:01,870 --> 00:42:02,980
I kind of missed you today.

839
00:42:02,980 --> 00:42:03,920
Don't know why.

840
00:42:03,930 --> 00:42:09,020
♪ And pou'd the gowans fine ♪

841
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:05,350
Hurry up.

842
00:42:05,380 --> 00:42:07,000
We have to go eat noodles after this.

843
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:07,800
Liang.

844
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:10,190
Mr. Tao, stop putting on airs.

845
00:42:10,210 --> 00:42:11,230
Hurry up. We're waiting for you.

846
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:16,150
♪ But we've wander'd monie a weary fit ♪

847
00:42:11,300 --> 00:42:11,670
Come on

848
00:42:11,670 --> 00:42:13,030
-Come on.
-Hurry.

849
00:42:11,850 --> 00:42:15,630
[Seasons Change Hostel]

850
00:42:16,530 --> 00:42:21,890
♪ Sin' auld lang syne ♪

851
00:42:24,660 --> 00:42:30,320
♪ For auld lang syne, my dear ♪

852
00:42:27,550 --> 00:42:28,750
5-second countdown.

853
00:42:29,400 --> 00:42:30,050
5.

854
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:33,850
[Seasons Change Hostel]

855
00:42:30,860 --> 00:42:31,510
4.

856
00:42:30,950 --> 00:42:36,890
♪ For auld lang syne ♪

857
00:42:31,980 --> 00:42:32,630
3.

858
00:42:33,260 --> 00:42:33,920
2.

859
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:35,530
1.

860
00:42:35,900 --> 00:42:38,780
Seasons Change Hostel!

861
00:42:36,010 --> 00:42:39,010
[Seasons Change Hostel]

862
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:43,150
♪ We'll tak a cup o' kindness yet ♪

863
00:42:43,580 --> 00:42:49,250
♪ For auld lang syne ♪
